job_description:
Responsibilities:
• You will develop and enhance biometric enrollment and identification product;

• You will maintain and support existing biometric enrollment and identification product and troubleshoot current production system issues;

• You will develop new client/web applications;

• You will configure, fine-tune deploy the solution on test/production environment (local and client site);

• You will understand and adhere to design and coding procedures and standards;

• You will write the technical documentations

Requirements:
• Bachelor's degree in Computer Engineering or equivalent

• Minimum of 5 years of web frontend development

• Good knowledge of Java, Javascript (ES6), CSS, HTML5, Flex

• Experienced with other web application frameworks (React, Angular or Vue)

• Experienced with object oriented C# libraries, w3 SOAP services, WPF

• Knowledge of some of the scripting languages, Maven, Git, SVN & Jira

• Willingness to travel for workshops, integration and deployment in customer premises (time spent abroad up to 20%)
